<subSubSection id="539875051A7E4C1C760B1A0A907080DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph id="25D5C9167A91B5C59C6FEED977D573D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6607F1EC20BE3D9DD8679C320789852D" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="5E07459ED5ACDF5900B3DF9FA689CA6A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
Male 
<emphasis id="438942E9C9D744209848B5AAA442DAC2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Holotype</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(ICN-Ao-1976). Measurements. TL (ChL+DSL): 4.45, DSL: 2.66, CL: 1.07, CW: 1.79, AL: 1.59, AW: 2.21, BaCh: 0.55. Pedipalp: Tr: 0.60, Fe: 1.23, Pa: 0.72, Ti: 0.88, Ta: 0.70, Claw: 0.79. Leg I: Tr: 0.42, Fe: 4.10, Pa: 0.73, Ti: 3.19, Mt: 5.86, Ta: 1.31, TL: 15.61; Leg II: Tr: 0.57, Fe: 9.21, Pa: 0.98, Ti: 7.67, Mt: 12.40, Ta: 5.14, TL: 35.97. Leg III: Tr: 0.62, Fe: 5.92, Pa: 0.97, Ti: 3.65, Mt: 7.52, Ta: 1.58, TL: 20.26. Leg IV: Tr: 0.70, Fe: 8.65, Pa: 1.00, Ti: 4.85, Mt: 11.14, Ta: 1.82, TL: 28.16.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C896D6A68E63930B06EF132FC66135D" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="76484598F8EC10BB2978F7B7A3A1F1F3" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Dorsum.</emphasis>
DS Epsilon type 2. Anterior and lateral margins of DS smooth. Ocularium low, smooth, and without median concavity (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E65DECB7EA05E177C7BCB85A418092C8" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in panoramic (A), dorsal (B), ventral (C), lateral (D), and frontal (E) views. Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 1 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647183" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">1A, B, E</figureCitation>
). Mesotergum slightly delimited, divided into four smooth areas: area I divided into two halves; areas II-IV undivided (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="46D825A4D256723917583C749AD4F1E2" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Drawings of Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views. Left coxa I in ventral view (C). Right chelicera in frontal view (D). Left pedipalp in ventral view (E). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D, E); 0.5 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647184" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">2A</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of scutum substraight and with few granules (Figs 
<figureCitation id="BA76CC8D0C1054E0CCAB57353A5CEA87" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in panoramic (A), dorsal (B), ventral (C), lateral (D), and frontal (E) views. Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 1 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647183" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FE8BE5549B09D722E658EAC67848942D" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Drawings of Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views. Left coxa I in ventral view (C). Right chelicera in frontal view (D). Left pedipalp in ventral view (E). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D, E); 0.5 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647184" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">2B</figureCitation>
). Free tergites I-III with some granules (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FA89DB0C967F7A5E63C9BD5D9F074F48" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in panoramic (A), dorsal (B), ventral (C), lateral (D), and frontal (E) views. Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 1 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647183" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">1B, D, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="7D88B8A30B91FC70B5DCBD273B4366B1" doi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647183" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="2BF9044DF85D8FBE5EE38C191E52F4C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="735B9A467BE9032A6083FF26A60D9AA4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Figure 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4A4C2872EDDE8A467CE257EC9882D5F9" authorityName="García &amp; Vargas &amp; Estrada" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Agoristenidae" genus="Avima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Avima wayuunaiki" order="Opiliones" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wayuunaiki">
<emphasis id="EB1616CA183A81B5E49436E310379CB6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Avima wayuunaiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (ICN-Ao-1976), male holotype. Habitus in panoramic (
<emphasis id="56598EEB18AD0AE3DAD1067526129520" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">A</emphasis>
), dorsal (
<emphasis id="D25132AD6865891537534FB1C4DA8096" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">B</emphasis>
), ventral (
<emphasis id="527DFF9BCE20B585B29516D3AD1EE108" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">C</emphasis>
), lateral (
<emphasis id="C49662CC2248AFD48C4D4733D112C80B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">D</emphasis>
), and frontal (
<emphasis id="D59E0B447DD042A94098925A095ECCA6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">E</emphasis>
) views. Scale bars: 2 mm (
<emphasis id="629707305A6ADC4DFD75F3CFC50552BF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">A</emphasis>
); 1 mm (
<emphasis id="E729081BFC61E20490C0D1B7F267D9D2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">B-E</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="57593887E388DA7F9CEE3F19F502FAE6" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="85E04C526F1F5D009B34D8058DC902F4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="34AD5CD0D6920C04B1DACAFAB646C442" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Venter</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Coxa I with a longitudinal row of tubercles and one large bicapitate tubercle on the anteroproximal margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="31ADB08B17642397ADD3E63990CD4E61" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Drawings of Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views. Left coxa I in ventral view (C). Right chelicera in frontal view (D). Left pedipalp in ventral view (E). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D, E); 0.5 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647184" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">2C</figureCitation>
); coxae II-IV with some granules; coxa II longer than coxa I; coxa III longer than coxae I and II; coxa IV backward projected. Stigmata oval, small and transverse (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6DE7C6077EC74CA77EE3EAF5BA85B9DD" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in panoramic (A), dorsal (B), ventral (C), lateral (D), and frontal (E) views. Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 1 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647183" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="AB16990DBBEF7C60E575B4DD9FD7F25A" doi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647184" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="D178D803039E77F26DF9FB7E7E0919BB" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="FE05136D570215F10B836784BFE64A69" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Figure 2.</emphasis>
Drawings of 
<taxonomicName id="FAD1F38218D9F3727E14D3CBA0FED02B" authorityName="García &amp; Vargas &amp; Estrada" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Agoristenidae" genus="Avima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Avima wayuunaiki" order="Opiliones" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wayuunaiki">
<emphasis id="9DC571B7ABBAAB929ECAEDFF960987D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Avima wayuunaiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (ICN-Ao-1976), male holotype. Habitus in dorsal (
<emphasis id="A83AE31A01C4DE1C9C1D2EC40A666425" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">A</emphasis>
) and lateral (
<emphasis id="E81849FCD2E5BE38675DF45BF7D5C370" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">B</emphasis>
) views. Left coxa I in ventral view (
<emphasis id="D65807F8C54BE781EF7CB7491004BDB7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">C</emphasis>
). Right chelicera in frontal view (
<emphasis id="6D4448DF96FBDBB71F8D356715BB9C30" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">D</emphasis>
). Left pedipalp in ventral view (
<emphasis id="2ABB8F5BCAC015534EC86250A5C382A9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">E</emphasis>
). Scale bars: 1 mm (
<emphasis id="AFEDC0734565179A0227B36FB52A3428" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">A, B, D, E</emphasis>
); 0.5 mm (
<emphasis id="6879615CB1EEE1C79163C9F67665401B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">C</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="1EDA5BA0711BA187C245C55C2BB7DBCD" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="706152D35EBD2A0EFDB8745B1778A925" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="671AF67CC58A466A1A16AD876D2A10E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Chelicera</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Chelicera swollen. BaCh quadrate in dorsal view, with well-marked bulla, three mesal, five anterior, and three ectal tubercles. Hand with setiferous tubercles of different sizes reaching the medial and posterior region. Fixed finger with the inner surface finely grooved. Movable finger with one trapezoid, small, sub-basal tooth, and with a dentate distal inner surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1C60C1DF708F76E6D69B53F9E068A3C7" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Drawings of Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views. Left coxa I in ventral view (C). Right chelicera in frontal view (D). Left pedipalp in ventral view (E). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D, E); 0.5 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647184" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">2D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B084AC6E7650A9B0BFAEFAA312A2B8D" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="E458979488C0CF8646714C70DEEEB16A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="AF40F4156515C4C8F5EF45C7FEB4C58E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Pedipalps</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
All segments more slender than usual (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B58063F1714A53D4A118C0C709E4BFFA" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in panoramic (A), dorsal (B), ventral (C), lateral (D), and frontal (E) views. Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 1 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647183" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">1B</figureCitation>
). Trochanter with one subapical tubercle on the ventral face. Femur with a ventroectal row of four setiferous tubercles (the two basalmost largest and the two distalmost medium-sized), and one large ventromesal setiferous tubercle in the apical portion (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="06AD20BDE7D196BF903ED9005E8A8876" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Drawings of Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) views. Left coxa I in ventral view (C). Right chelicera in frontal view (D). Left pedipalp in ventral view (E). Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D, E); 0.5 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647184" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">2E</figureCitation>
). Patella with one large mesal setiferous tubercle. Tibia ectal III, mesal IIi. Tarsus ectal IIi, mesal IIi.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A55188F3748C1AF6359B701A1382B094" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="868A8466165861033069A364B57B5005" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="68E9A9EE77361333289E25C77BF520BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Legs</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Increasing in thickness from leg I to leg IV, all smooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8B70615EDA4E8E3BE9621FB48792CD8F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in panoramic (A), dorsal (B), ventral (C), lateral (D), and frontal (E) views. Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 1 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647183" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">1A</figureCitation>
). Leg I filiform; coxae I-III with one dorsoanterior and one dorso-posterior tubercle; Coxa IV with some prolaterodistal tubercles; Fe III-IV darker than I-II. Fe IV length three and a half times DS length (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B9F9D411A55CE02E10990209C5674345" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in panoramic (A), dorsal (B), ventral (C), lateral (D), and frontal (E) views. Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 1 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647183" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">1A</figureCitation>
); Ta I-II each with one smooth claw; Ta III-IV with two subparallel smooth claws and without tarsal process. Tarsal counts: 9(3)-9(3)/19(3)-18(3)/7-6/7-7.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D862BD91F93DD3716201AC10252A197A" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="123B1521C3A6F46B4CD06001EA5ED59C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="18E81843323FC2287AC444AB02E4DFD4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Penis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
LP small (width twice the height) and apically depressed, with anterolateral acute corners (crescent-shaped) apically pointed (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6664756875AB633250159E42778A7EDD" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. SEM of the male genitalia of Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1718), paratype. Distal portion of the penis in lateroapical (A), dorsoapical (B), lateral (C), ventral (D), and oblique (E) views; detail of stylus in lateral view (F). Abbreviations: MS = Macrosetae. Scale bars: 50 µm (A-E); 10 µm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647185" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">3A-E</figureCitation>
). Malleus with two pairs of branched MS-A, being MS-A2 far from the base of the stylus; one pair of branched MS-B; MS-C absent; two pairs of medium-sized MS-D located in a keel between the dorsal region of the LP and the base of the stylus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4F1E3576514249461BCB7B603D8414F4" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. SEM of the male genitalia of Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1718), paratype. Distal portion of the penis in lateroapical (A), dorsoapical (B), lateral (C), ventral (D), and oblique (E) views; detail of stylus in lateral view (F). Abbreviations: MS = Macrosetae. Scale bars: 50 µm (A-E); 10 µm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647185" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">3A-C, E</figureCitation>
); MS-E2 large and branched, MS-E1 short and conical, located slightly distal to MS-E2 on the ventral side of the LP (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C99D89D30A6C27C058474EC1E9EC255A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. SEM of the male genitalia of Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1718), paratype. Distal portion of the penis in lateroapical (A), dorsoapical (B), lateral (C), ventral (D), and oblique (E) views; detail of stylus in lateral view (F). Abbreviations: MS = Macrosetae. Scale bars: 50 µm (A-E); 10 µm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647185" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">3C, D</figureCitation>
). Stylus elongated, mostly straight (concave at the apex), and surpassing the LP; dorsal keel present, smooth, elevated at the medial region, with a dorsoapical sharp projection; tip dorsally projected (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="36D7D409E8FD81CEC421D1460AAC5F36" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. SEM of the male genitalia of Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1718), paratype. Distal portion of the penis in lateroapical (A), dorsoapical (B), lateral (C), ventral (D), and oblique (E) views; detail of stylus in lateral view (F). Abbreviations: MS = Macrosetae. Scale bars: 50 µm (A-E); 10 µm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647185" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">3E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="E6B76384A47D6474B342D7371786A2C9" doi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647185" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph id="228313509FF4DED04B9A9345326F07B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="5AA86051AF1C2F73B4A1AB447FD7A6B4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Figure 3.</emphasis>
SEM of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="B196658E5073603F161DF839B01ACC64" authorityName="García &amp; Vargas &amp; Estrada" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Agoristenidae" genus="Avima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Avima wayuunaiki" order="Opiliones" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wayuunaiki">
<emphasis id="385A0EA0615D44FEC5E9BA4716425C92" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Avima wayuunaiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (ICN-Ao-1718), paratype. Distal portion of the penis in lateroapical (
<emphasis id="60178291342D8B66F6917FBEACCC94AD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">A</emphasis>
), dorsoapical (
<emphasis id="DA9E29DD3FE877B30B98201420EAE5DA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">B</emphasis>
), lateral (
<emphasis id="B7B2AD447AF68C5B25274510206BD155" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">C</emphasis>
), ventral (
<emphasis id="AA19D9437DD5386470FA2D4201038060" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">D</emphasis>
), and oblique (
<emphasis id="0573ED4A65BA70F548E289F530DEB02C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">E</emphasis>
) views; detail of stylus in lateral view (
<emphasis id="41CB257557593DFC8F93E9C7097F1CBD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">F</emphasis>
). Abbreviations: MS = Macrosetae. Scale bars: 50 
<normalizedToken id="5C0693ABE269A76E3CAD7383233E401B" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="376905A5AC6E894418FC241EA3A11A93" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">A-E</emphasis>
); 10 
<normalizedToken id="7EFC22F3EC5386BC821D3AEC55AB5A94" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="FD803FCA031A67E9C1F231E8113EFA84" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">F</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="3AC2BE678450772DC34D4355251E088E" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="E2F5B3975CD52F1D7CBE6D68B99C9391" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Color (in alcohol).</emphasis>
DS and chelicerae Light Yellow (86). Pedipalps, coxae, and trochanters I-IV Pale Yellow (89). Femora to tarsi I-IV Dark Yellowish Brown (78) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="69764D5916461D8944E25CFF0F8BDE5F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. (ICN-Ao- 1976), male holotype. Habitus in panoramic (A), dorsal (B), ventral (C), lateral (D), and frontal (E) views. Scale bars: 2 mm (A); 1 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647183" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="747C33FE2FBC037E283F6F5369E87228" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="AD086117293259E9C57E8659DC0715F5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Female.</emphasis>
Paratype (ICN-Ao-1718). Similar to male, except for abdomen wider at areas II-III, chelicerae not swollen, and leg IV slender. Measurements: TL (Ch+DSL): 3.50, DSL: 2.35, CL: 0.96, CW: 1.61, AL: 1.39, AW: 1.96, BaCh: 0.42. Pedipalp: Tr: 0.41, Fe: 1.12, Pa: 0.65, Ti: 0.84, Ta: 0.79, Claw: 0.78. Leg I: Tr: 0.32, Fe: 4.27, Pa: 0.69, Ti: 3.19, Mt: 6.04, Ta: 1.29, TL: 15.8; Leg II: Tr: 0.39, Fe: 9.53, Pa: 0.98, Ti: 8.70, Mt: 12.14, Ta: 5.34, TL: 37.08. Leg III: Tr: 0.39, Fe: 9.36, Pa: 1.04, Ti: 5.77, Mt: 13.25, Ta: 1.51, TL: 31.32. Leg IV: Tr: 0.68, Fe: 8.70, Pa: 0.94, Ti: 4.83, Mt: 11.08, Ta: 1.80, TL: 28.03. Tarsal counts:?-6(3)/? -18(3)/6-6/7-6.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="142901AF6C9492B4CDE554331BE29B41" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F60EA4F11B8F04E87E93C37144F79464" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B16963E589CE12A42F713E5DF3EB8B1F" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Wayuunaiki is the language spoken by the indigenous Wayuu people in northwestern Venezuela and northeastern Colombia on the Guajira Peninsula, where the species was collected. Noun in apposition.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BE7914E8E6D66499C580BA769F6D8CDD" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="natural history">
<paragraph id="27140499D34478C89EFED04BA43649F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Natural history.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D7B94D793771B3D103B43159448B257" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="C2B845A1D971E668C44DFE3DF84317CD" genus="A." lsidName="A. wayuunaiki" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="wayuunaiki">
<emphasis id="A3DBB2000FDDA0FED0369EBC7BCF0F5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">A. wayuunaiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. were found inside a cave (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5BD933895D4647E91CD74A85A6D5B193" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Geographic distribution of Avima venezuelica, Avima troglobia and Avima wayuunaiki sp. nov. in Northern South America. A. Map with previous and new records of the species in Colombia and Venezuela (colored areas represent the WWF ecoregions (Olson et al. 2001 )); B. Banaderos cave in La Guajira (Colombia), habitat of A. wayuunaiki sp. nov.; C. Living specimen of A. wayuunaiki sp. nov. Photographs by Miguel Gutierrez Estrada (B), and Alex Gonzalez Vargas (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.78202.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647188" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">6B, C</figureCitation>
) in the northeastern slopes of Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta. This species lives sympatrically with 
<taxonomicName id="22DC57AC073EADED62ECD131B4F6FDF1" authorityName="Cala-Riquelme, Gutierrez-Estrada &amp; Florez" authorityYear="2015" class="Arachnida" family="Sicariidae" genus="Loxosceles" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Loxosceles guajira" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guajira">
<emphasis id="F09FBC0C2EC5962F28DAD5F87BA74B12" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Loxosceles guajira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cala-Riquelme, 
<normalizedToken id="27FA75A2F9A9C77F616B1B32258C13A0" originalValue="Gutiérrez-Estrada">Gutierrez-Estrada</normalizedToken>
&amp; 
<normalizedToken id="83ABE23BC5736BF6D36F76AD1D0C652B" originalValue="Flórez">Florez</normalizedToken>
, 2015 (
<taxonomicName id="29E962AD5866CDFCDE1A53E6534512FB" authorityName="Keyserling" authorityYear="1880" class="Arachnida" family="Sicariidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sicariidae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="B55B6B3B3FCD78F1A45CE6195D17A54B" authorityName="DoNascimiento &amp; Prada-Pedreros" authorityYear="2020" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" genus="Trichomycterus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trichomycterus spectrum" order="Siluriformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spectrum">
<emphasis id="C69545A6C8EB3D090B5E6C6DC806468C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Trichomycterus spectrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
DoNascimiento &amp; Prada-Pedreros, 2020 (
<taxonomicName id="170DDCE8006EEB950A73CC08F1493BC5" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1858" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichomycteridae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Siluriformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Trichomycteridae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
